<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-04-27T11:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-04-27T11:30:00-05:00" n="740" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d740">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3131/405: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Scott</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Caracas</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-04-27T12:00:00-04:30">April 27,
                                    1939—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:39 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>41. From Daniels.<note n="2" xml:id="d740fn2">Paul C. Daniels, Foreign
                                Service officer on special mission to Venezuela in connection with
                                trade-agreement negotiations.</note> Does the Department desire any
                            action to be taken with respect to the <hi rend="italic">modus
                                vivendi</hi> which is due to expire next May 11? If the trade
                            agreement is signed by that date obviously no action is necessary but
                            this is beginning to appear doubtful. Neither the Foreign Office nor I
                            have raised this question as yet. [Daniels.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Scott</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>